It doesn't have to be DND specifically, just trying to think of a small step where it's ok to be weird that's just once a week to start. Beating depression is a marathon not a sprint, if you find something you enjoy that you can do every day right off the bat you'll become addicted to the feeling of being happy and if that thing is taken from you, or you have to take a break from it, you'll fall in to an even deeper depression when you don't have it, so just starting slow with something you do once weekly to be happy is a good way to start. Ease yourself in to being content being the norm with intermittent happiness sprinkled in. It's not easy, but it's not impossible, all you have to do is make the first move and take it one day at a time. Until you do it, it won't happen, no one is going to do it for you.
